  <!-- Why Nitrogen Purging -->
  <h2 id="nitrogen-purging">Why Nitrogen Purging?</h2>

  <p>
    When a centrifuge processes sludge containing flammable solvents, the high-speed rotating bowl creates centrifugal aerosolization and off-gassing of volatile organic compounds. In standard centrifuges, these vapors can accumulate to ignitable concentrations inside the casing. The CHNX 418 addresses this risk by continuously flowing inert nitrogen gas through the bowl cavity and discharge areas, displacing any oxygen and preventing combustible mixtures from forming.
  </p>
  <p>
    This approach is recognized by ATEX standards as an effective protective measure for centrifuge applications in Zone 1 and Zone 2 hazardous locations. Contact our engineering team to discuss whether the CHNX 418 or another <a href="/explosion-proof-centrifuge/">explosion-proof centrifuge</a> configuration is appropriate for your specific solvents and process conditions. See also our <a href="/decanter-centrifuge/">decanter centrifuge</a> overview and <a href="/decanter-centrifuge-applications/">decanter centrifuge applications</a> for broader context.
  </p>

